#{\footnote about}${\footnote About the Nonogram Solver}
K{\footnote About the Nonogram Solver}+{\footnote Overviews:01}
\pard\keepn\f4\fs30\b About the Nonogram Solver\par
\pard\plain\f4\fs20
\par
\par
The Nonogram Solver is a special program designed to solve the Nonogram
 puzzles found in the Sunday Telegraph newspaper. The program can be used
 to:\par
\par
\tx360\li360\fi-360
{\f1\'B7}
\tab Interactively enter Nonogram data.\par
{\f1\'B7}
\tab Load Nonogram data from a data file.\par
{\f1\'B7}
\tab Solve Nonogram data.\par
{\f1\'B7}
\tab Save Nonogram data to a file.\par
{\f1\'B7}
\tab Print Nonograms.\par
\pard
\par
This help file is for version 2.3 of the Nonogram solver program\f4\fs18
  (NONOGRAM.EXE)\f4\fs20  which was released on the 15th of November 1994. If the
 version of the Nonogram Solver that you are using is not version 2.3
 then the information in this help file may be incorrect.\par
\par
To check the version of the Nonogram Solver program select
\f4\fs18  HELP|ABOUT\f4\fs20  from the main menu.\par
\par
\par
\par\f4\fs24\b
Also see
\par\plain\f4\fs20\uldb
Contents\plain \v\f4 main_contents\plain\par \f4\fs20\uldb
What are Nonograms?\plain\uldb\v whatare\plain\uldb\f4\fs20\par
A quick introduction\plain\uldb\v quickintro\plain\uldb\f4\fs20\par
The main window\plain\uldb\v mainwindow\plain\uldb\f4\fs20\par
