#{\footnote solvedata}${\footnote Solve a Nonogram}
K{\footnote Solve a Nonogram}+{\footnote Howto:02}
\pard\keepn\f4\fs30\b Solve a Nonogram\par
\pard\plain\f4\fs20
\par
\par
To solve a Nonogram either select\f4\fs18  OPTIONS|SOLVE\f4\fs20  from the main menu or
 click the solve tool bar button:\par
\par
\tab{\f2\cf2 \{bmc solvicon.bmp\}}\par
\par
The data is automatically checked for consistency and if it passes this
 check it is then solved using the selected solution options. The main
 window title changes while the data is being solved and the solve tool
 bar button changes to the stop solve tool bar button:\par
\par
\tab{\f2\cf2 \{bmc stopicon.bmp\}}\par
\par
The status bar is also updated to indicate that a solution is taking
 place: if the solution is successful then the status bar will contain
 the text\f4\fs18  'Successfully solved'\f4\fs20  otherwise it will be
 \f4\fs18  'Cannot obtain a solution!'.\par 
\par
If a solution cannot be found it may be that the solution options that
 are currently selected are not suitable: see the \uldb Configure 
 Solution\v confsolu\plain\f4\fs20  help option for more information.\par
\par
\par
