#{\footnote savedata}${\footnote Save a data file}
K{\footnote Save a data file}+{\footnote Howto:04}
\pard\keepn\f4\fs30\b Save a data file\par
\pard\plain\f4\fs20
\par
\par
You can save a data file by either selecting\f4\fs18  FILE|SAVE\f4\fs20  from the main
 menu as shown below:\par
\par
{\f2\cf2 \{bmc savemenu.bmp\}}\par
\par
or by clicking on the save tool bar button:\par
\par
\tab{\f2\cf2 \{bmc saveicon.bmp\}}\par
\par
If the file does not have a name yet you will be asked to choose a name
 for the file. Choose\f4\fs18  FILE|SAVE AS...\f4\fs20  from the main menu to save a data
 file under a different name.\par
\par
\par\f4\fs24\b
Note:\par\plain\f4\fs20
\par
Data files are stored in a plain ASCII format (such as those produced using NOTEPAD etc). 
The format is of one title line, followed by the puzzle data. The puzzle will be in the 
form of a MxN grid and the data for the side of M must is stored first, followed by that 
for the side of N. \par
\par
For example:\par
\par \f0\fs18
White Rabbit Nonogram\tab \_ \f8\fs20 - Title line\par \f0\fs18
20 25\tab \tab \tab \tab \_ \f8\fs20 - Nonogram size information\par \f0\fs18
1 2 10 2\tab \tab \tab \_ \f8\fs20 - First line of data out of block of N\par \f0\fs18
2 3 2 4\tab \tab \tab \_ \f8\fs20 - Second line of data out of block of N\par \f0\fs18
3 4 1 6\tab \tab \tab \_ \f8\fs20 - Third line of data out of block of N\par \f0\fs18
: : : :  : \tab \tab \tab \_ \f8\fs20 - Another (M+N-4) rows of data\par \f0\fs18
4 5 3 11\tab \tab \tab \_ \f8\fs20 - Nth line of data out of block of N\par \f0\fs18
\par\plain\f4\fs20
Note also that the default file extension for Nonogram data files is '.NGM'.\par
\par
\par
